<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4344/–5.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Chargé <persName type="to">Heimké</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 50.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 139, of December 29, 1906, relative to the claim of Ricardo
                            A. Deeb, an American citizen, for losses sustained during the late civil
                            war in the United States of Colombia.</p>
                        <p>The department approves the action of the legation in respect to this
                            case.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>